SIMPLE: shrill
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shrill
<hw>Shrill</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Shriller</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Shrillest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>shril</ets>,
<ets>schril</ets>; akin to LG. <ets>schrell</ets>, G.
<ets>schrill</ets>. See <er>Shrill</er>,<pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety>
<def>Acute; sharp; piercing; having or emitting a sharp, piercing tone
or sound; -- said of a sound, or of that which produces a
sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hear the <qex>shrill</qex> whistle which doth order give⟦br⟧
To sounds confused.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let winds be <qex>shrill</qex>, let waves roll high.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shrill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shrill
<hw>Shrill</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shrill sound.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shrill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Shrill
<hw>Shrill</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Shrilled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Shrilling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>schrillen</ets>, akin
to G. <ets>schrillen</ets>; cf. AS. <ets>scralletan</ets> to resound
loudly, Icel. <ets>skr⟦oum⟧lta</ets> to jolt, Sw. <ets>skr⟦aum⟧lla</ets>
to shrill, Norw. <ets>skryla</ets>, <ets>skr<?/la</ets>. Cf.
<er>Skirl</er>.]</ety> <def>To utter an acute, piercing sound; to sound
with a sharp, shrill tone; to become shrill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Break we our pipes, that <qex>shrilled</qex>loud as lark.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No sounds were heard but of the <qex>shrilling</qex> cock.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His voice <qex>shrilled</qex> with passion.</q> <rj><qau>L.
Wallace.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shrill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Shrill
<hw>Shrill</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To utter or express in a shrill
tone; to cause to make a shrill sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How poor Andromache <qex>shrills</qex> her dolors forth.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shrill-gorged</ent>⟦br⟧
